# ai-tell-allow.txt — discipline terminology allowlist for ai-tell.sh
#
# One lowercased term per line. Any term listed here is NOT flagged as
# machine-prose by ai-tell.sh. Use it for words that are legitimate, load-bearing
# jargon in YOUR field but happen to be on the generic "AI tell" list.
#
# Inline comments after '#' are ignored, so you can annotate why.
# A per-project override lives at <project>/.ai-tell-allow.txt (same format);
# both files are merged.
#
# Examples — uncomment the ones that apply to your discipline:
# robust          # statistics / ML: "robust standard errors", "robustness check"
# leverage        # finance: "leverage ratio"; physics: "lever arm"
# significant     # statistics: "statistically significant" (still watch for vague use)
# paramount       # law
# foster          # social work / education: "foster care", "foster engagement"
# realm           # mathematics/physics when literal, not figurative
